---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="methodology — siteatlas">
  <h1>methodology</h1>
  <p>
    siteatlas presents project data with confidence scores from 0 to 100.
    the score reflects the volume and independence of underlying evidence:
    queue filings, county permits, equipment orders, satellite imagery,
    and trade or local press coverage.
  </p>

  <h2>confidence bands</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>0 to 30 (red):</strong> thin paper trail; treat as rumor until corroborated.</li>
    <li><strong>31 to 60 (amber):</strong> partial documentation; one or two independent filings.</li>
    <li><strong>61 to 100 (green):</strong> multiple cross-checked filings; the project is on the public record.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>evidence types</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>permit:</strong> a county or municipal filing tied to the site.</li>
    <li><strong>queue:</strong> an interconnection queue position with the grid operator.</li>
    <li><strong>equipment_order:</strong> a transformer, switchgear, or substation order.</li>
    <li><strong>satellite:</strong> public imagery showing site work.</li>
    <li><strong>news:</strong> trade or local press coverage with a checkable byline.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>data source</h2>
  <p>
    v0.1 ships a committed synthetic fixture at
    <code>src/data/ercot.fixture.json</code>. v0.2 swaps in a symlink to
    a real upstream export by changing one constant in
    <code>astro.config.mjs</code>. the typed loader at
    <code>src/lib/load-projects.ts</code> fails the build on schema
    drift, naming the offending slug and field.
  </p>

  <h2>voice charter</h2>
  <p>
    the rule lists for the voice gate live in
    <code>decisions/voice-charter.json</code>. the human narrative of the
    three rules lives in <code>decisions/DEC-001-civic-voice-charter.md</code>.
    edits to the json change gate behavior; edits to the markdown do
    not.
  </p>

  <h2>scope</h2>
  <p>
    v0.1 covers ercot large-load queue projects only. an rss change feed,
    a broken-link gate, and an accessibility gate are deferred to spec 0003.
  </p>
</Base>
